Investigative Support Analyst - USAID / U.S. Embassy - Islamabad
Islamabad
United States Agency for International Development (USAID) Mission to Pakistan is soliciting applications for the following position for its Islamabad office:
Investigation (Investigative Support Analyst)
For detailed position description and posting of online application, interested applicants may visit our website: http://islamabad.usembassy.gov/employment_opportunities.html. Applications must be submitted on form DS-174 (Application for Employment as LE Staff), which can be accessed from the above website.
Applications can be submitted either by email on FSNIslamabad@usaid.gov or by postal mail on the below address:
HR Unit, Executive Office
USAID/Pakistan, U.S. Embassy
Ramna 5, Diplomatic Enclave
Islamabad 44000, Pakistan.
If application is submitted by email, the title of the position must be mentioned in the subject line. In case of postal mail, please mark application envelop with position title on the top right of the envelope. Applications should be sent only once either by email or by postal mail. Deadline for submission of applications is May 8, 2014.
